16:21:11 [INFO]   Recovered JSON from error on data:text/plain,MSc program “Biomedical Engineering and Technology”
Department of Biomedical Engineering
University of West Attica
Agiou Spyridonos, 12243 Egaleo, Athens, Greece
Phone: +30 210 538 5855
Email: bmet.msc@uniwa.gr
Call for applications for the academic year 2026 - 2027
1. Program at a glance
The MSc in “Biomedical Engineering and Technology” is a 1.5-year postgraduate program (90
ECTS) conducted in English by the Department of Biomedical Engineering of the University of
West Attica, Greece.
Target group:
Individuals holding a Bachelor's (B.Sc.) degree in engineering, technology, life sciences, health
sciences, or related fields, who seek a career change in Biomedical Engineering.
Program’s goals:
a/ to intensively introduce the science of biomedical engineering,
b/ to develop problem-solving skills,
c/ to actively engage with the biomedical engineering industry,
d/ to prepare students for Ph.D. studies.
Teaching staff:
 Invited professors from 8 different Universities (Greece, Portugal, Spain, Romania,
Germany, UK, USA),
 Invited Researchers from biomedical engineering research facilities,
 Invited Biomedical Engineers from the labor market.
Special cooperation agreement with the University of Plymouth, UK
Students have the option to spend one semester at the University of Plymouth, UK, under
privileged terms and conditions. They can earn a second MSc diploma in 'Medical Engineering'
alongside the MSc diploma in 'Biomedical Engineering and Technology' from UniWA. For more
information, visit the official program website.
2. Program format
Studies start: October 2026 (the weekly schedule for the 1st semester will be announced in late
September 2026)
Duration: 1.5 years (3 academic semesters), 90 ECTS
Teaching language: English
1
The MSc program is delivered in a blended format. During the first two semesters, lectures are
primarily online, except for the final month of each semester, when activities requiring physical
presence in Athens take place, including laboratories, exams, site visits, and demonstrations. No
online alternative is available for these activities. During the third semester, students are
required to complete their diploma thesis. Depending on the topic, the thesis may be conducted
with physical presence, fully online, or in a blended format.
For certain online courses, a hybrid option may be offered, allowing some students to attend in
person while others join online, depending on organizational considerations.
3. Admissions procedure
The selection of postgraduate students will take place in two application rounds, provided that
the maximum number of admitted students, who have secured their place as described below,
is not reached during the first round.
First round
First round application period: 01 April - 31 May 2026 1
Interview period: 02-05 June 2026 (online) 1
Announcement of preliminary evaluation results: 08-12 June 2026 1
Deposit to secure your place (non-refundable): After the announcement of the evaluation
results, successful applicants are required to pay a non-refundable deposit of €500 by 30 June
2026 in order to secure their place.
Student registration: 28 September - 09 October 2026, physical presence mandatory, there is no
online registration option available.
English language test: 03 June 2026, 12:00 – 14:00 (Athens time) (online). Only for those who do not hold
at least B2 level English certification. 1
Second round (only if the maximum number of students has not been filled during the first-round)
Second round application period: 24 August - 11 September 2026 1
Interview period: 15-18 September 2026 (online) 1
Announcement of preliminary evaluation results: 21-23 September 2026 1
Deposit to secure your place (non-refundable): After the announcement of the evaluation
results, successful applicants are required to pay a non-refundable deposit of €500 by 28
September 2026 in order to secure their place.
Student registration: 28 September - 09 October 2026, physical presence mandatory, there is no
online registration option available.
English language test: 15 September 2026, 12:00 – 14:00 (Athens time) (online). Only for those who do not
hold at least B2 level English certification. 1
1 Should there be an extension of the application submission deadline, the timelines for interviews, English
language tests, and the announcement of final results may be subject to change accordingly.
2
Tuition fees: 2000 €
The fees are payable in three instalments as follows:
 1st instalment to secure your place (non-refundable even if you do not complete
registration): 500 € – payable by 30/06/2026.
 1st instalment for successful registration: 500 € – payable during the student registration
period. Registration is considered valid only after payment of this instalment 2.
 2nd instalment: 500 € – payable by 31/10/2026.
 3rd instalment: 500 € – payable by 30/11/2026.
IMPORTANT NOTICE!
According to the study regulations, the MSc program will be organized provided that the
minimum number of participants, which is 10 students, is reached. In the event that the MSc
program is not conducted due to failure to meet the minimum required number of students, the
tuition fee installments already paid by the newly enrolled students shall be refunded.
4. Online meetings for interested candidates
Online meetings for interested candidates will be held on the following dates:
 07/04/2026, 17:00 (Athens time) (Current time zone offset in Athens: UTC/GMT +3:00
hours), (to participate click on this link and request to join)
 19/05/2026, 17:00 (Athens time) (Current time zone offset in Athens: UTC/GMT +3:00
hours), (to participate click on this link and request to join)
Subscribe to our newsletter for email reminders about these meetings.
5. Required documents
1. Undergraduate/bachelor degree certification (compulsory)
2. Transcript of records including the list of the courses’ grades (compulsory)
3. Academic recognition of the Undergraduate/bachelor degree by the Hellenic National
Recognition and Information Center (NARIC/DOATAP) (if any, only for holders of non-Greek
University degrees)
4. English language certification, at least B2 (compulsory) or application for written and oral
English exam (compulsory) (The English language test for applicants that do not hold B2 or higher
English language certification will be organized 03 June 2026, 12:00-14:00. Participants will
receive a follow-up email with further details regarding the platform and login instructions)
5. CV according to the Europass template (max 3 pages) (compulsory)
6. Motivation letter (max 2 pages) (Tell us at least the following: a/ why you would like to study
biomedical engineering, b/ what do you expect to achieve after the completion of the program,
