information
Duration of Study
18 months.
Delivery method
• Fully on line format: All semesters delivered through
synchronous and/or asynchronous distance learning
methods, in Athens, Greece.
• Blended format: The first two semesters delivered
in situ, in Athens, Greece, and the remaining third
Applications
semester offered using synchronous and/or asynchro-
until
nous distance learning methods.
Aug 31st
• Fully in situ format: All three semesters delivered
in Athens, Greece.
2026
Tuition fees
4.000 € per semester | 12.000 € in total. Flexible pay-
ment options:
Pay in Advance:
Secure your place in the program by paying the total
tuition fee upfront.
Instalment Plan:
Spread the cost over three equal instalments, payable
at the beginning of each semester for your convenience.
Visa for non-EU citizens
For students attending the Programme in situ or in a
blended-learning format, enrolment in the MSc “Leader-
ship: Ethics and Politics” makes non-EU citizens eligible for a
VISA D – category H.1 (Schengen mobility) for a 12 months
stay in Greece. The administration of the Program will supply
students all necessary documents and facilitate successful
visa application process.
How to apply
Visit the program’s website and follow the instructions.
Contact either the Secretariat or the Admissions Team
for any inquiry.
