INTERDEPARTMENTAL PROGRAM OF GRADUATE STUDIES
“Science, Technology, Society—
Science and Technology Studies”
Call for Applications, Academic Year 2026-2027
Application Period: from March 16 to June 30 (2026)
sts.phs.uoa.gr
Webpage:
16.03.2026
The Department of History and Philosophy of Science and the Department of Informatics
and Telecommunications of the National and Kapodistrian University of Athens organize and
offer the Interdepartmental Program of Graduate Studies in “Science, Technology, Society—
Science and Technology Studies”. The Program provides interdisciplinary education on
issues related to science, technology and medicine with the aim of highlighting the best
options in critical fields, such as artificial intelligence, algorithms and big data, as well as all
information and telecommunications sciences and technologies, sciences and technologies
aimed at addressing the environmental crisis, biology, medicine, biotechnology and
biomedical technology. The curriculum includes mandatory and elective courses or modules
on the relationship of science, technology and medicine with society, politics, economics,
work, ethics, law, gender, disability, borders and migration, literature and art, as well as on
the education and public image of science, technology and medicine, and the history,
philosophy, sociology and anthropology of science, technology and medicine. The graduate
program takes advantage of long-standing collaborations with international university
networks, such as ESST (www.esst.eu) and CIVIS (https://civis.eu/en).
Submission of the application and the supporting documents: from March 16 to June 30,
2026. The evaluation of applications will take place in two periods: end of April (A) and end
of June (B). The use of period A is encouraged for applications from candidates from
countries that require a lengthy visa process.
The Official Gazette of the operation of the Program is 6224/27-10-2023. The duration of the
Program is set at two (2) semesters minimum, and four (4) semesters maximum. Attendance
at the Program requires the payment of a tuition fee of one thousand (1,000.00) euros (five
hundred for each semester of study). Up to 30% of the total number of students admitted to
the Program are exempt from tuition fees based on the relevant legislation. This Call concerns
the admission of up to thirty-six (36) students to the program for the academic year 2026–
2027. During their studies, they are required to successfully attend ten (10) courses or seven
(7) courses and to prepare a thesis. The courses are conducted in English. The Program admits
holders of degree from cycle A studies, from all Departments of Greek universities, or from
equivalent foreign institutions, recognized by the Hellenic National Academic Recognition
Information Center (NARIC, ΔΟΑΤΑΠ), as well as graduates of all Departments of Greek
universities or recognized foreign ones. It also admits, on the top of the number mentioned
above (36 students), members of special categories of the academic community (ΕΕΠ, ΕΔΙΠ,
ΕΤΕΠ), according to article 34, paragraph 8, of the relevant law. The certificate of recognition
of the degree from NARIC must be submitted before graduation from the program.
APPLICATION DOCUMENTS
1. Application
2. Curriculum Vitae
3. Copy of degree or confirmation of completion of studies
4. Transcripts
5. Peer reviewed publications, if any
6. Proofs of professional or research activity, if any
7. Copy of state ID (front and back)
8. Two (2) recommendation letters
9. Certificate of knowledge of the English language, level B2 or above
For international (non-Greek) applicants: You may submit electronically the application
form (signed), the CV and the certified copy of degree or confirmation of completion of
studies (please send them to sts@phs.uoa.gr) and we will contact you regarding the
submission of the rest of the application material.
For information about the application to the Program:
Secretariat of the Department of History and Philosophy of Science
Tel: 210 7275590
For information about the Program: tympas@phs.uoa.gr or sts@phs.uoa.gr
The Director of the Interdepartmental Program of Graduate Studies
Professor Aristotle Tympas
email: tympas@phs.uoa.gr
